The base race idea originally came from Wolfenstein Enemy Territory map, and I created a version of it for Counter Strike: Source.

in the game the team must steal the other team's flag (like capture the flag), bring it back to base an upgrade part of the base.
I made 7 upgradable things with 3 upgrades each which are:
gate
front wall
left wall
right wall
back wall
armory
medical center

you must play this map with deathmatch mod.

this is still a beta version an it may be laggy, there are few known bugs:
-nades's damage can bypass upgraded walls.
-the rain sound may not work on the second round.

Also there is a twist with the gameplay, team members can pick up their on flag and carry it around (but can't upgrade their on base with it of course).

lacking stuff that I'll add to later versions:
-sounds
-when one team upgrade all upgrades to the max, the other team dies (and the round is over).
-fix bugs.
make the flag to return to base when member of its own team touch it(only if the twist won't be liked).

I made this map for the marble track mapping contest made by Lost (http://www.fpsbanana.com/threads/121387?206). 

Of all the maps i've made, i've never had a map that was more of a pain in the ass than this one. Overall, it took about 44 hours of work to perfect and I had to compile it 36 times to get it right. Each time before this final compile, it had problems, such as leaks, stretched textures, the marbles would fall off the track, the map would crash the server, the map wouldn't be optimized enough and wouldn't look right, the track wouldn't be made correctly and the marble would get stuck on it. After fixing and compiling it 36 times I finally got it to look semi-good and work perfectly. 

I would also like to thank crazypip666 for making the marble prop, mekaonija and icecreamlock for making the custom textures used in my map, and karatekaefer for making the custom skybox texture. Thanks to all 4 of you for helping make my map work, and look, great.


TO INSTALL THIS MAP:
To install the map to be used in game, download the map (sorry the file is kinda big) and save it to this folder: C:\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\<username>\counter-strike source. Then once it's saved and downloaded to that location, go into that folder and find the downloaded .rar file and extract it there, it will then extract and place the map files into the appropriate folders by itself.

TO PLAY THE MAP IN GAME: 
There is 2 ways I know of to do this, one is to click "create server". Then once you've clicked that a box will pop up, find the map in the map selection box. Don't add any bots to the game. Then click the "Start" Button at the bottom of the box. This will load the map and allow you to watch the marbles go down the track.
The second way to do this is to open consol and type "map bros_marble_superspin" in consol then press enter, this way (imo) is much easier than going through the whole create server thing.

CS:S BREAKOUT_V2 by SUPA.

The Atari 2600, originally called the Atari VCS (Video Computer System) is the godfather of modern video game systems, and helped found the video game industry. Atari released the Atari VCS in October 1977 with nine games. This system would come to dominate the industry for many years. Atari sold over thirty million of the consoles, and together with other companies sold hundreds of millions of games. Atari continued to release games for the 2600 and in 1978 gave us Breakout.

So now with the power of the source engine we go back to the beginning of it all. I am pleased to present you with Breakout for Counter-Strike: Source. This the merging of the dig/breakfloor/glass type concepts with a source physics based ball in play.

Version 2 Specifics:

In this more themed version you are inside a monitor playing a game of breakout. The bricks are your floor, and is slowly (and sometimes quickly) being destroyed from under you. You must reach and eliminate the other team. A game score is kept for the amount blocks that have been destroyed during gameplay. Since the wall blocks are tougher they are worth 5 points.

Outside the monitor is an Atari equipped with 6 switches, some of which can be shot through the glass to affect gameplay. You must have good aim and a powerful bullet to toggle them.

   wall hp : reduces hp of wall bricks by 1000
   left hp : reduces hp of counter-terrorist floor bricks by half
  right hp : reduces hp of terrorist floor bricks by half
multi-ball : add two more dangerous balls to the game

The two other switches must be activated in person either by teleport or noclip. There is also a notch by the Breakout cart you can use to control the paddle.

I would like to thank wolf for the tree and fern models that decorate the breakout_v2 skybox and Tstar for making breakfloor design that breakout_v1 builds upon. If your interested in some scaled down versions of the Atari models for use in other maps let me know. I can only hope this release will inspire other mappers to revive more old classic games for us in source.

Supa 

~~~~~~

Yokai's Side Notes: 
 I remember when Supa first posted this map on Interlopers a few months ago and remembered me saying "that has to be one of the most unique maps I have seen in a long long time." I now have server that switches onto the map every once and a while depending on vote/mapcycle. 

My ratings:

Graphics = 5/5
Game Play = 4/5
Sounds = 4/5
Overall : 86%, A must try.

Breakfloor2011
By Helix.

This map is a 2011 version of breakfloor. The map is totally retextured and has a nice orange ambient in it. The map is more detailed and the shoutout "break the floor" has been revamped. Also, the bottom of the pit has been redesigned. If players somehow survive the drop, they will still die because everybody gets dissolved on the bottom. 

Note that the amount of layers have been reduced from 5 to 4. That is because of an engine error (yay 4 update) and it couldn't stack so many func_breakables anymore.

The amount of spawnpoints have been increased to 56. (28 on each team).

So go and get your updated version of breakfloor! I hope the breakfloor players are settled for the upcoming year. :)


Enjoy!
Helix.
